Git commands :

git clone
git init
git pull
git diff
git add .
git status
git stash/commit
git log 
git push
git branch task1
git branch task2
git checkout task2
git merge task1
git log
git checkout -b task3
git branch -a
git tag

**********************************************************************************************************************************

Git commands with their description :

1. git init -> to create new repository.
2. git add . / git add filename -> add changes from working directory to staging area.
3. git status -> listing all changed or added files.
4. git log -> Show commit logs with stats like who did, where , time ,etc .
5. git config --list -> list all the details or verify configuration also other configurations will be displayed as well.
6. git pull -> to update local branch with remote repository changes.
7. git commit -m "message" -> to commit your staged changes.
8. git push -> push all branches to remote repository .
9. git clone -> create a local copy of a remote repository.
10. git fetch -> check for the changes in local or remote repository.
11. git commit --amend -m "message" -> appending changes to already committed files.
12. git branch branchname -> to create a new branch.
13. git checkout branchname -> switch to different branch.
14. git checkout -b branchname -> create & switch to new branch.
15. git branch -> list all the branches.
16. git branch -d branchname -> delete a branch from repository.
17. git diff -> to check the changes or differences whit are yet to be committed.
18. git diff branch1 branch2 -> to check differences between 2 branches.
19.  merging a branch with another ->
	git checkout destination_branch
	git merge branch_to_merge   
20. git diff sourcebranch targetbranch -> to preview changes before merging.
21. git revert -> undo a public commit.
22. git remote add origin __ -> connect to local repository to remote repository.
23. git remote -v -> listing all currently configured remote repositories.
24. git tag -> listing all tags.
25. git tag -d tagname -> delete local tag.
26. git reset: Undo commits by moving branch reference.
27. git branch -a -> list all branches.
28. git reset --soft HEAD~1 -> rollback to staging area.
29. git reset --hard HEAD~1 -> delete the current head by 1 commit.
	 ( prefer only soft HEAD)

